      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Nerd as Stereotype</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard Boverie letter says July 27 article linking high attrition rate for women in computer science to fears about nerd stereotype is demeaning to women</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The article about declining numbers of women majoring in computer science carried a quotation saying that ''the image of the white, male, antisocial nerd who sits in front of a computer turns women off.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The article about declining numbers of women majoring in computer science carried a quotation saying that ''the image of the white, male, antisocial nerd who sits in front of a computer turns women off.''</p>
        <p>As an excuse for the high attrition rate for women in computer science, the comment implies, at least to me, that women are shallow. I think that is demeaning to women.</p>
        <p>RICHARD BOVERIE  West Palm Beach, Fla.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
